reviews.text: Great place to get fresh organic vegetables!  The staff is friendly and accommodating offering up advice and details on their farming skills.  The farm stand is self-service with nice displays of freshly picked vegetables.  Worth a stop when in the area!
Self service farm stand and CSA. Beautiful location and offer reasonably price plants, including perennials and veg garden plants.
Amazing fresh veggies and really good rye bread. This is a CSA based business.
I love this farm.  We get our veggies here.  The no-till farming is impressive.  Plus there's kittens.

The home of my CSA. Spendy but you get what you get: choice of your vegetables, herbs and flowers to round out your meal and dinner table respectively. Beyond that, it's idyllic and the kittens running around are just part of the fun.

Address: 133 Flag Pond Rd, Saco, ME 04072, USA

placeDetails.name: Ives Berry Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 133 Flag Pond Rd, Saco, ME 04072, USA

reviews.text: Had the best time! Such a beautiful and tranquil blueberry orchard! So appreciate Wayne and his family’s hospitality. Loved the delicious berries! Enjoyed tasting such a wide variety— who knew! Great value for a beautiful delicious experience!
Impressive operation, super fun picking with my son today, look forward to next year's crop, thank you for your hard work!
Small wonderful pick-your-own blueberry farm. Like 7 different varieties. Nice
Beautiful tasty berries, many varieties, nice family farm!
In all ways, just lovely.

What a gem!   Enormous selection of the widest variety of pumpkins and gourds I've ever seen.  Mums were beautiful and  everything priced better than anyone around.    Step inside and you'll be greeted by the owner's friendly coworkers, his beautiful dogs!   We look forward to going back!

I’d give it zero if I could. Most of the Veggies were rotted with fruit flies everywhere. When I tried to check the produce in the bushel because of how awful other items were the man said “I don’t need to sell that to you, I can sell it to someone else.” I’m assuming bc I kept looking.  I explain I’m a disabled vet and my brain struggles to process  but he was rude anyway. I’ll never return nor recommend this place to anyone! Went to Meservey about 5 miles away  (thanks to another reviewer) and the produce was AMAZINGLY fresh and the gentleman who came out to help was so super kind!

There was a FB Marketplace ad for 10 lbs of wild blueberries for $28. What a great deal right? We walked in and there were 4 people sitting at a table and they didn't even look up. We came to check out the blueberries so we opened up a box. They were stored in a carboard shoe box shaped box. We opened the first two boxes and they had mold growing on the top of the blueberries. We didn't buy them. Some ads are too good to be true. The other food items they sold were not good looking either. I noticed that someone said that this was a good place as an alternative to grocery stores. I disagree. If you buy here, you're buying stuff that in a couple days would go to the pigs. Support another local farm (there are plenty) that has good and fresh produce and the price is honest. After leaving here, I went to Meservey Farms and picked up a lb of FRESH green beans and a couple zucchini for $3.50. Other farms I would recommend are Snell and Frugal Farmers.

I wish I took pictures of the blueberries to post but I thought that would be rude when I was there. Honestly I should have because the people there wouldn't have noticed.
Down to earth market.  Not fancy. But nice fresh produce and good prices. Great place to supplement grocery budget with fruit and vegetables.
Great plants. Awesome prices.  Fantastic Produce.  Year after year after year.

reviews.text: What a charming place! I went early in the morning on a weekday and had the place almost to myself. The staff was very personable and the prices were super reasonable.

Best place in southern ME to pick strawberries 🍓
Love the friendly staff!
Had alot of fun picking with the grands, i  thinks i ate as much as i picked, lol always fun memories, just need some coolwhip later and yummy!!!!
We look forward to coming every year!
Great place!! We took our daughter today for her 1st Birthday! She had so much fun picking and tasting! Big red stained smiles! Very clean and well maintained fields! Thank you!

Name: Libby & Son U Picks
Address: 86 Sawyer Mountain Rd, Limerick, ME 04048, USA

placeDetails.name: Libby & Son U Picks
placeDetails.formatted_address: 86 Sawyer Mountain Rd, Limerick, ME 04048, USA

reviews.text:
🍎🍏🍎🍏🍎 Forgot five stars; this place gets five apples! 🍏✨ What a fun place to go with family or friends. No kids needed to enjoy this place! 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 My husband and I drove up on a Saturday afternoon. We started with lunch at our favorite food truck, Meet on the Street, and some delicious adult ciders. 🍻 Because it’s fall, y’all—why not! 🍂🍁 Next, this well-run operation had golf carts to drive you to the field. 🚜 We enjoyed apple 🍏 and blueberry picking. They were the best blueberries we’ve ever hand-picked! 🫐💙 We will definitely return next year for some of their other fruit options. On the way out, we picked up a few cider donuts. 🍩 Enjoy them right away when they’re hot! They will melt in your mouth. 😋

**Travel note:** 📱 You'll lose cell service, so plan your journey before you leave. Follow the travel tips on Libby's website. Your phone might lie to you! 🗺️🚗

I've missed Blueberry season last few years returning home to visit family, so when I saw Libby's was still open, we had to go. We got 10 lbs blueberries and 2 bags apples for a little over $100. But it was worth it because you can't find the flavor anywhere else across the states. My BFF and I had an amazing time and experience to last a lifetime. Clean place, friendly staff, and beautiful scenery.

I’ll preface this by saying we were three grown men who decided to go blueberry picking while visiting Maine (because you can’t do that in Missouri)….and we had a great time.  It was beautiful being out into he blueberry and raspberry fields.  The staff was super nice.  There was live music (but the beer truck wasn’t open). The fresh smoothies were delicious…as were the berries!   Well worth the drive from Portland.

Best apple picking experience we’ve ever had. Food trucks were awesome. Donuts and cider was even better. We loved the live music and the chauffeured golf cart rides to the orchard. This place has got it figured out!

Beautiful farm and beautiful fruit. The only downfall I would say would be how everything is priced because it would be difficult for a big family to come and enjoy themselves because pricing is based on how many people are in your group. Other then the way it's priced I would have given a 5 star because it is a nice orchard.

Name: Orchard Ridge Farm
Address: 236 Sebago Lake Rd, Gorham, ME 04038, USA

placeDetails.name: Orchard Ridge Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 236 Sebago Lake Rd, Gorham, ME 04038, USA

reviews.text: Went on a first date here. And it was amazing. Sadly, the apple picking was dwindling down. And the apples got some weather damage.  But we found a couple. The property is beautiful 😍.  Just a walk through the orchard was so peaceful. The shop had some yummy coffee drinks too! Service there is so friendly.

Popped into this super cute spot for the first time since the new owners took over, and I’m so glad I did! The menu is packed with options—whether you're in the mood for a breakfast sandwich, a hot latte, fresh bagels, pizza, a burger, or even a salad. Plus, they’ve got all sorts of fun pantry goodies, gifts, beer, wine, fresh eggs, and some chilled and frozen items.

While you wait for your food, you can wander outside to say hey to the chickens, goats, donkey, and pig!

We decided to hang out and had lunch at the big table that fits 4-6 people. We tried a little bit of everything: breakfast sandwich, pizza, burger, and falafel wrap. Everything was soooo tasty! There are also a couple of bar seats if you want to grab a quick bite. Can’t wait to come back!

Well....the orchard had only 2 varieties of apples. For $3 per pound, I expected a lot more. And, I was sad to see the animals' living conditions. The chickens were too crowded in their pen, the 2 goats didn't have any grazing area to speak of, and the one pig had no water in its small pen. There was a friendly rabbit hopping around.

The store was very nice, with lots of gourmet goodies and an impressive array of meats. The one staff person we saw was very friendly.  A nice display of pumpkins was outside.  But their website offered a much better experience!

Great big tasty blueberries and lots of them in a manicured idyllic setting. Friendly people, reasonable pricing, and a really wonderful bakery that had some of the best hot scones we have ever had. Easily recommended and 5 stars!

Really enjoyed staying here overnight in my camper and sampling some yummy meals and also enjoyed watching families enjoy immersing themselves in the experience of apple picking and friendly encounters with farm animals. Also, they are decorated for Halloween and have beautiful pumpkins and marigolds for sale. The apple trees were prolific but unfortunately the recent hurricane toppled some trees and lost many apples to the ground early.  The farm is lovely and right on the Sebago to sea greenway which I took advantage of with my dog. My dog is good with farm animals but still, I kept her up because of the food service & young families ( There is a playground and lawn games in the picnic area too). The staff work hard and are friendly and helpful. Market has an abundant variety of homegrown fresh foods and treats!
